com.analog.lyric.options

Class OptionRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.analog.lyric.options.OptionRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<IOptionKey<?>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DimpleOptionRegistry

    @ThreadSafe
public class OptionRegistry
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<IOptionKey<?>>
    A registry of known option keys indexed by qualified name.

    For use in looking up option keys by string either for use in configuration files or in implementing external APIs (e.g. MATLAB).

      • autoLoadKeys

        public boolean autoLoadKeys()
        If true, registry will attempt to automatically load fully qualified keys from classes.

        For instance, if attempting to get key for the string:

        "com.mycompany.MyOptions.myOption"
        the registry will automatically load all option keys declared in the class MyOptions. This will only work for fully qualified names whose classes are on the class path.

        This attribute is set in the constructor.

        Since:
        0.07

      • get

        @Nullable
public IOptionKey<?> get(java.lang.String name)
        Returns option key with specified name or null if not found.

        If autoLoadKeys() is enabled and name is a full canonical name then the key will be loaded automatically by loading the class and adding all of its declared options.

        Parameters:
        name - is either the canonical name or qualified name of the option.
        Throws:
        AmbiguousOptionNameException - if more than one possible option key matches the given name. This will not happen if a canonical name is used. The list of possible matches can be found in the exception.
        Since:
        0.07
        See Also:
        OptionKey.canonicalName(IOptionKey)
